                <p>HISTORY (established, opened, closed, etc.)</p>
                <p>C est. 4/19/43, Open 4/20/43 - Closed to Public 8/16/49 - Officially 9/27/49</p>
                <p>REMARKS:</p>
                <p>PB MEMO NOS. 376</p>
                <p>DEPT.CONTACTS</p>
                <table>
                    <row role="label">
                        <cell>DATE</cell>
                        <cell>ACTION, COMMUNICATIONS, REMARKS, ETC.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>1/4/43</cell>
                        <cell>DEPTEL drafted - est. on a temporary basis functioning under Embassy,
                            no separate consular district. DEPTEL 11/28/42 to Embassy re functioning
                            under supervision of CG at Kunming where practicable in purely consular
                            functions. Tihwa in old Hankow District. (F.S.List shows Sinkiang Prov.
                            in Hankow Dist., after opening Tihwa - 9/30/43 edition)</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>7/2/43</cell>
                        <cell>Desp. 1316 from Chungking--enclosure states "I considered that I has
                            assumed my functions as Consul at Tihwa as of the opening of business
                            the same day (Apr/20/43" Since Tihwa's permanent office and living
                            quarters had been</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </div>
